2026 Regular Session ENROLLED
SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 111
BY SENATOR CLOUD
A RESOLUTION
To commend and acknowledge the volunteers and members of the 2026 Concerned Women
for America's Encourage-A-Legislator Project.
WHEREAS, Concerned Women for America (CWA) is the nation's largest public
policy women's organization with a rich history of over forty years of helping its members
across the country bring Biblical principles into all levels of public policy; and
WHEREAS, 1 Timothy 2:1-2 instructs us to pray for our leaders, and CWA's
Encourage-A-Legislator (EAL) program offers members and friends the vehicle to do this
in an easy and meaningful way by ensuring consistent prayer for each legislator; and
WHEREAS, as prayers are offered on behalf of the legislators, hearts are changed
and encouraged; and
WHEREAS, the goal of the EAL program is to encourage each member of the state
legislature, as well as statewide office holders, by praying for them on a regular basis; and
WHEREAS, the EAL program is a great way to lift up persons in authority and
encourage them in their responsibilities; and
WHEREAS, it is highly appropriate to commend the volunteers and members of the
2026 Concerned Women for America's Encourage-A-Legislator Project.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
does hereby commend and acknowledge the volunteers and members of the 2026 Concerned
Women for America's Encourage-A-Legislator Project.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to Laura
Huber of Concerned Women for America of Louisiana.
PRESIDENT OF THE SENATE
